Feline fans in the area can now pet kittens as they sip coffee and munch on homemade chocolate, sticky ginger, and cherry and walnut cake.

Ms Harrison thought of opening Willows Cat Cafe after hearing that cafes featuring cats were doing brisk business in London, New York and Tokyo.

She said: 'I knew it was popular so I thought it could definitely work.

'People may think it's unusual but for me it was a completely natural idea to bring to the shelter.

The cafe is open every Monday from 11am to 2pm. 30 to 45 minute slots are available to visitors.  

'You do need to book ahead - we have to have some sort of structure otherwise it would just be manic,' Ms Harrison said. 

