'Me and my sister, both cat lovers just decide to come down and support the adoption centre and it's absolutely lovely,' said a visitor. 

'Even if you can't have a cat for yourself it's just nice to come down and spend a little time with the cats. It's really good fun,' she continued.  

Cat cafes first took off in Japan 10 years ago, and have since been established in areas across the UK.  

 

 

